  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dc0 \u0db4\u0dcf\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0dc3\u0dcf\u0d9a\u0da0\u0dca\u0da1\u0dcf \u0d87\u0dbb\u0dd0\u0db9\u0dd9\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "All-party talks begin",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The President's Office states that three rounds of negotiations with the main political parties regarding the formation of an all-party government were held today under the chairmanship of Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe.",
        "Party leaders and members representing the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna and the ruling party attended the first round of discussions and the second discussion was held with the Ceylon Labor Congress. Ceylon Labor Congress Leader Sendhil Thondaman and its General Secretary Member of Parliament Jeevan Thondaman and other representatives participated in it.",
        "The third discussion was held with the National Congress and its leader Member of Parliament A.L.M. A delegation including Ataullah participated in it.",
        "The President's Office says that the President is going to discuss the formation of an all-party government with several parties tomorrow (03) and many parties including Samagi Jana Balawegaya, Sri Lanka Freedom Party, Tamil National Alliance have expressed their agreement to join the future talks.",
        "President Ranil Wickramasinghe said that religious leaders led by the Maha Sangharatna, civil organizations, youth groups and the entire people have strong confidence and expectation about an all-party government.",
        "Prime Minister Dinesh Gunawardena, President's Secretary Saman Ekanayake, President's Additional Secretary Lawyer Chaminda Kularatne and others also participated in this discussion."
      ],
